1
00:01:29,740 --> 00:01:34,940
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,410 --> 00:01:37,789
[Episode 22]

3
00:01:56,789 --> 00:01:57,640
Are you okay?

4
00:01:59,860 --> 00:02:00,650
I'm fine.

5
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:02,660
How did the talk go?

6
00:02:04,230 --> 00:02:06,070
It was just an initial meeting.

7
00:02:06,590 --> 00:02:08,250
He insisted on your presence.

8
00:02:08,470 --> 00:02:09,690
He left when you didn't return.

9
00:02:09,690 --> 00:02:11,150
We didn't talk about much.

10
00:02:14,480 --> 00:02:15,770
Can you tell me

11
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:17,660
what happened?

12
00:02:20,079 --> 00:02:22,079
He was my business partner back then.

13
00:02:22,079 --> 00:02:23,810
We started a company together.

14
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:26,240
He took all my money

15
00:02:26,470 --> 00:02:27,240
just to save

16
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:30,370
Jiangnan Machinery Plant,
which he's about to sell now.

17
00:02:30,500 --> 00:02:31,760
Ridiculous, isn't it?

18
00:02:39,230 --> 00:02:41,090
You should stay off this project.

19
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,290
I'll go talk to Mr. Kong.

20
00:02:42,290 --> 00:02:43,020
And say what?

21
00:02:44,590 --> 00:02:47,050
That I can't face the person
who deceived me?

22
00:02:49,430 --> 00:02:50,890
I'm not who I was back then.

23
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:56,630
Lei.

24
00:02:58,340 --> 00:02:59,750
Pretending you don't see me?

25
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:01,110
I've been waiting for you for ages.

26
00:03:01,110 --> 00:03:02,110
Let's have a chat.

27
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:15,120
All these years, you ignored my calls

28
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,600
and my text messages.

29
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:19,630
You have to give me a chance to explain.

30
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:22,079
If we hadn't run into each other at Fenlier,

31
00:03:22,079 --> 00:03:23,800
would we never have met again?

32
00:03:26,590 --> 00:03:27,150
I've already calculated

33
00:03:27,150 --> 00:03:29,430
your shares in Jiangnan Machinery Plant.

34
00:03:29,430 --> 00:03:31,030
Not a single cent less than
what you deserve.

35
00:03:31,030 --> 00:03:32,690
I just misappropriated them.

36
00:03:35,190 --> 00:03:36,450
What about my website?

37
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:39,590
A website is just a way to make money.

38
00:03:40,030 --> 00:03:42,090
Isn't our ultimate goal to make money?

39
00:03:42,090 --> 00:03:44,890
We can make money just the same
in a different form.

40
00:03:46,470 --> 00:03:49,270
You say I have shares
in Jiangnan Machinery Plant.

41
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,400
But I've read the documents.

42
00:03:51,710 --> 00:03:53,710
The shareholders are all named Fan.

43
00:03:55,280 --> 00:03:56,740
It's our family business.

44
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:59,850
It's not appropriate to list other names.

45
00:03:59,910 --> 00:04:02,240
They wouldn't agree to it, right?

46
00:04:02,590 --> 00:04:04,790
I'm holding your shares on your behalf.

47
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,010
On my behalf?

48
00:04:07,890 --> 00:04:10,480
So, we just take your word for it?

49
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:12,330
I'm really not lying to you.

50
00:04:13,150 --> 00:04:15,210
I can accept that our startup failed.

51
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:17,600
I can also accept an ending where
our differences cannot be reconciled,

52
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:18,950
and we go our separate ways.

53
00:04:18,950 --> 00:04:20,510
Even running out of funds

54
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:22,240
and going bankrupt...

55
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:24,250
I can accept all of that.

56
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:27,360
But I absolutely cannot accept that

57
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:29,950
you sold the website behind my back.

58
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:31,920
How about this...

59
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:34,480
You say you didn't lie to me.

60
00:04:34,940 --> 00:04:36,600
Do you think I'd believe that?

61
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:39,360
Let's sign a contract.

62
00:04:39,670 --> 00:04:40,460
Write an IOU.

63
00:04:41,310 --> 00:04:42,560
We'll prove that these shares are yours,

64
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:43,890
and that I owe you money.

65
00:04:43,990 --> 00:04:45,250
Does that work for you?

66
00:04:46,190 --> 00:04:47,430
I'm the acquirer now.

67
00:04:48,310 --> 00:04:50,070
If I sign any contract with you

68
00:04:50,070 --> 00:04:50,950
or take an IOU,

69
00:04:51,190 --> 00:04:52,950
wouldn't I be falling into your trap?

70
00:04:52,950 --> 00:04:53,870
This won't work, that won't do...

71
00:04:53,870 --> 00:04:55,200
Then give me a solution.

72
00:04:57,680 --> 00:04:58,950
Anyway, during this period,

73
00:04:58,950 --> 00:05:00,000
let's not talk about anything.

74
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,400
Not a word about the past.

75
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:03,080
When I sold the website,

76
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:04,120
I had no choice.

77
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:06,480
I couldn't just sit and watch

78
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:08,190
our family business go under, could I?

79
00:05:08,190 --> 00:05:09,480
Would I still be human if I did?

80
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:11,210
So you're human for doing this?

81
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:14,750
Do you know how much blood and sweat

82
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:16,310
I poured into this website?

83
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,600
It was my hope

84
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:18,680
and my future!

85
00:05:18,950 --> 00:05:19,600
And then?

86
00:05:21,390 --> 00:05:22,600
You ruined it.

87
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:23,160
I'm sorry.

88
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,690
Don't tell me you're sorry.

89
00:05:24,830 --> 00:05:26,560
Let me tell you something else.

90
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:28,680
Do you think I'm angry with you

91
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:30,410
because you didn't pay me back?

92
00:05:31,190 --> 00:05:33,190
Or because of your bullshit shares?

93
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:40,930
How about this?
You can raise the acquisition price a bit

94
00:05:40,950 --> 00:05:42,080
to solve my problem.

95
00:05:42,190 --> 00:05:43,960
You can also complete your task this way.

96
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:45,020
After I make money,

97
00:05:45,190 --> 00:05:47,040
I'll take the money out
and start another website.

98
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,900
It kills two birds with one stone.

99
00:05:49,070 --> 00:05:50,470
I'm a fastidious person.

100
00:05:55,020 --> 00:05:56,430
Made up your mind?

101
00:05:57,560 --> 00:06:00,270
I didn't come here for Maeda.

102
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:03,160
Then what do you want from me?

103
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:05,190
I came for Zhang Xiaoman.

104
00:06:05,590 --> 00:06:06,440
For him?

105
00:06:08,030 --> 00:06:09,270
What is he to you?

106
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,950
Although we're not really related,

107
00:06:11,950 --> 00:06:13,430
no matter what,

108
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,390
he is my employee.

109
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,400
So why are you looking for me?

110
00:06:20,070 --> 00:06:21,630
I want to ask you

111
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:24,360
not to arrange matches for Zhang Xiaoman.

112
00:06:25,310 --> 00:06:26,910
Not arrange matches for him?

113
00:06:27,190 --> 00:06:28,750
I spent time and money training him,

114
00:06:28,750 --> 00:06:30,610
and you don't want him to compete?

115
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,700
Why should I listen to you?

116
00:06:35,310 --> 00:06:36,430
Mr. Watanabe,

117
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:39,800
you have so many excellent fighters here.

118
00:06:41,630 --> 00:06:43,360
You spent a lot of money on him.

119
00:06:43,630 --> 00:06:46,090
I'll pay you back
on Zhang Xiaoman's behalf.

120
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:47,510
I don't need that.

121
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,560
You don't understand him.

122
00:06:50,430 --> 00:06:52,430
He is my new cash cow.

123
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,480
You won't give me
Maeda's championship belt,

124
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:57,340
so how am I supposed to make money?

125
00:06:58,950 --> 00:07:01,150
His business has nothing to do with you.

126
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:03,120
If I give it to you, will that be enough?

127
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:05,950
Zhang Xiaoman doesn't understand
the meaning of these matches.

128
00:07:05,950 --> 00:07:07,830
Are you trying to ruin him?

129
00:07:08,310 --> 00:07:11,310
I don't need these things anymore.

130
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,560
Xiaoman is more valuable
than the championship belt.

131
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:17,200
How do you know the matches will ruin him?

132
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:19,310
Mr. Watanabe.

133
00:07:20,430 --> 00:07:22,160
That's what happened to Maeda,

134
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:22,800
isn't it?

135
00:07:24,490 --> 00:07:28,730
Many people die
all over the world every year.

136
00:07:29,690 --> 00:07:32,080
Do you think they didn't know the danger?

137
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:36,760
This is the path he chose himself.

138
00:07:36,909 --> 00:07:38,590
No one forced him.

139
00:07:41,950 --> 00:07:44,070
You bastard who only sees money!

140
00:07:47,330 --> 00:07:49,940
Money is the best reflection
of human nature.

141
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:57,430
Xiaoman,

142
00:07:57,750 --> 00:07:59,430
after finishing
the catenary structure studies,

143
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:01,560
we are starting to explore new fields.

144
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:03,000
I'm afraid I can't keep up,

145
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,930
so I even take my laptop to the café.

146
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:07,270
Sophie laughs at me

147
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:10,410
for not mastering
the essence of French relaxation.

148
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:12,200
I hope to see you soon.

149
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:14,510
Xiaodan,

150
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:17,160
they've assigned me
a professional coach now.

151
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:18,420
I've started training

152
00:08:18,830 --> 00:08:20,360
to prepare for the matches.

153
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:22,960
I hope to earn enough money
to go to France soon.

154
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:26,190
Xiaoman,

155
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:27,920
winter time is starting.

156
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:29,780
The days are getting shorter.

157
00:08:29,870 --> 00:08:31,730
I have less and less time to paint.

158
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:37,390
Xiaodan, Qu pickled some sauerkraut himself.

159
00:08:37,630 --> 00:08:39,840
Everyone made sauerkraut dumplings
for the New Year.

160
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:41,320
We wrote the Fu characters together

161
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,179
and put them up.

162
00:08:42,270 --> 00:08:43,480
It was so festive.

163
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:49,080
Xiaoman, it was my birthday.

164
00:08:49,270 --> 00:08:52,090
I borrowed a friend's phone
to check the time in Japan.

165
00:08:52,090 --> 00:08:54,690
But I still didn't receive
your birthday wish.

166
00:08:54,790 --> 00:08:56,600
Did you forget my birthday?

167
00:08:57,030 --> 00:08:59,080
I didn't get your midnight wish.

168
00:08:59,510 --> 00:09:00,830
Not at 9:17 either.

169
00:09:01,940 --> 00:09:04,340
But my friend made me
a candlelight dinner.

170
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:05,440
I remembered

171
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:07,770
the fireworks you set off for me back then.

172
00:09:08,110 --> 00:09:09,970
We even made dumplings together.

173
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:11,920
I wish you were by my side.

174
00:09:22,630 --> 00:09:24,670
Xiaoman, my design won a good ranking

175
00:09:24,670 --> 00:09:26,030
in the competition again.

176
00:09:26,030 --> 00:09:27,200
My friend Sophie,

177
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:28,630
Guoqing, and his girlfriend

178
00:09:28,630 --> 00:09:29,960
all celebrated with me.

179
00:09:31,290 --> 00:09:33,440
But I wanted your congratulations more.

180
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,770
What have you been up to?

181
00:09:35,070 --> 00:09:36,880
We haven't called in a long time.

182
00:10:05,940 --> 00:10:06,690
Xiaoman,

183
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:08,820
there was a riot in France.

184
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:10,540
Someone followed me home.

185
00:10:11,630 --> 00:10:12,630
Where are you?

186
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:14,200
I'm scared.

187
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:30,750
Xiaoman, I really want to hear your voice,

188
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:33,360
but I can't reach you no matter what.

189
00:10:42,550 --> 00:10:44,820
Xiaoman, what are you doing?

190
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:47,270
I call you, but no one answers.

191
00:10:47,870 --> 00:10:51,240
Your texts are always so short.
Are you okay?

192
00:10:51,670 --> 00:10:53,330
I'm really worried about you.

193
00:11:11,390 --> 00:11:12,480
Hello? Xiaoman?

194
00:11:12,830 --> 00:11:14,840
Xiaodan? You called?

195
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,330
I didn't see it just now.

196
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:17,880
What's wrong?

197
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,150
It's okay now.

198
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:21,720
What?

199
00:11:22,090 --> 00:11:24,840
Don't hit me while I'm talking. Hello?

200
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:25,720
Xiaoman?

201
00:11:26,060 --> 00:11:27,660
Why is it so noisy over there?

202
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:30,150
You heard that? Listen.

203
00:11:31,670 --> 00:11:34,320
You know what?
There was a homeless guy just now...

204
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:35,320
Did you hear that?

205
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:37,550
Hello?

206
00:11:41,270 --> 00:11:42,550
T-the signal here is too bad.

207
00:11:42,550 --> 00:11:43,790
Add two towers here.

208
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:46,960
Xiaoman.

209
00:11:47,550 --> 00:11:49,840
We haven't been in touch for a long time.

210
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:52,030
How are you?

211
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:55,790
You wouldn't let me visit you in Japan

212
00:11:56,030 --> 00:11:58,870
because you're worried
I'd be too busy with school.

213
00:11:58,870 --> 00:12:01,550
But I can't reach you. I'm really worried.

214
00:12:03,620 --> 00:12:05,280
I've decided to go to Japan...

215
00:12:06,450 --> 00:12:07,050
To see you.

216
00:12:17,810 --> 00:12:19,390
[International Arrivals]

217
00:12:44,710 --> 00:12:45,550
Xiaoman!

218
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:50,000
Xiaoman!

219
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:56,840
Xiaoman!

220
00:12:59,910 --> 00:13:00,910
Xiaoman...

221
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:34,920
It wasn't easy for you to save this much.

222
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:36,270
And you're giving it all to me?

223
00:13:36,270 --> 00:13:37,320
Just take it.

224
00:13:37,320 --> 00:13:38,390
What do I need it for?

225
00:13:38,390 --> 00:13:40,360
I have food, drinks,
and a place to stay here.

226
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:41,600
There's nowhere to spend it anyway.

227
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:43,150
Besides, I saved this money

228
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:45,510
just to invest in your dream.

229
00:13:46,670 --> 00:13:47,480
Xiaoman!

230
00:13:47,870 --> 00:13:52,120
Xiaoman!

231
00:13:52,910 --> 00:13:53,630
Xiaoman,

232
00:13:54,670 --> 00:13:56,200
have you heard this saying?

233
00:13:58,110 --> 00:14:00,400
"Insanity is doing the same thing

234
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:01,960
over and over

235
00:14:03,030 --> 00:14:05,030
and expecting different results."

236
00:14:08,790 --> 00:14:09,720
All this time,

237
00:14:10,550 --> 00:14:12,630
I've been running forward on my own.

238
00:14:13,960 --> 00:14:16,270
I selfishly refused to stop.

239
00:14:17,390 --> 00:14:19,720
Just because I yearned for a bigger world,

240
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:23,530
I forced you to do what I thought was right.

241
00:14:24,680 --> 00:14:27,350
I never considered what you wanted.

242
00:14:32,550 --> 00:14:34,080
But my Xiaoman,

243
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:38,810
you're the son of Western Tiecheng
who loves your hometown.

244
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:41,030
How could I make you leave your home for me

245
00:14:41,030 --> 00:14:42,560
and end up covered in scars?

246
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:45,640
I don't want to see you like this.

247
00:14:46,510 --> 00:14:47,270
I think

248
00:14:47,670 --> 00:14:49,630
we are just doing the same thing

249
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:51,360
over and over again.

250
00:14:51,790 --> 00:14:53,840
Maybe it’s time for us to wake up

251
00:14:54,630 --> 00:14:56,090
and live a different life.

252
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:01,670
We're all Chinese.

253
00:15:01,670 --> 00:15:03,120
If I could help, I would.

254
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:06,080
Is there really no other way?

255
00:15:06,390 --> 00:15:09,030
I've really done my best on this.

256
00:15:09,030 --> 00:15:12,120
Look, man, if it's too hard, just say so.

257
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:14,550
Here, take all of this.

258
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:16,670
You have to get this done for me.

259
00:15:16,670 --> 00:15:18,550
You have to make it happen, understand?

260
00:15:18,550 --> 00:15:19,480
It has to work.

261
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:21,200
What do you mean it won't work?

262
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:22,750
It's not about the money.

263
00:15:22,750 --> 00:15:25,510
I can handle all the paperwork for you,

264
00:15:25,510 --> 00:15:27,360
but I don't control the visas.

265
00:15:27,520 --> 00:15:29,720
If the French Embassy rejects it,

266
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,120
there's nothing I can do.

267
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:36,630
Don't... never mind that.

268
00:15:36,630 --> 00:15:37,630
Take this with you.

269
00:15:37,630 --> 00:15:38,120
Just go there one more time for me.

270
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:39,360
Try again for me, okay?

271
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:39,790
Take it all.

272
00:15:39,790 --> 00:15:40,870
If it's not enough, tell me. I have more.

273
00:15:40,870 --> 00:15:41,600
-No.
-Okay?

274
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,080
Brother, we're both Chinese.

275
00:15:43,080 --> 00:15:44,480
I really want to help you.

276
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:48,020
But their investigation says
you have immigration intent.

277
00:15:48,020 --> 00:15:51,040
Basically, they're afraid
you'd stay in France illegally.

278
00:15:51,040 --> 00:15:52,020
I...

279
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:53,770
I really can't help you.

280
00:16:59,630 --> 00:17:00,200
Hello?

281
00:17:00,840 --> 00:17:01,550
Xiaodan.

282
00:17:04,069 --> 00:17:04,920
Xiaoman.

283
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:20,589
So,

284
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:24,770
I've been thinking
these past couple of days.

285
00:17:24,829 --> 00:17:27,240
Since you studied design too,

286
00:17:28,590 --> 00:17:30,960
I was wondering if you'd want to

287
00:17:30,960 --> 00:17:32,510
come back to China to work.

288
00:17:32,900 --> 00:17:35,290
Beijing, Shanghai...

289
00:17:36,340 --> 00:17:38,070
They all need a talent like you.

290
00:17:38,710 --> 00:17:41,310
If not there, Japan works too.

291
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:43,640
What do you think?

292
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:46,310
I...

293
00:17:46,750 --> 00:17:47,640
received a job offer

294
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:49,590
from a design firm here.

295
00:18:00,070 --> 00:18:01,590
You found a job?

296
00:18:03,830 --> 00:18:04,890
That's great news.

297
00:18:06,030 --> 00:18:07,560
I have to congratulate you.

298
00:18:09,030 --> 00:18:11,790
You've finally become

299
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:14,790
a real designer.

300
00:18:17,430 --> 00:18:18,290
What about you?

301
00:18:28,550 --> 00:18:30,080
Take good care of yourself.

302
00:18:31,510 --> 00:18:32,910
Don't keep getting hurt.

303
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:33,830
I know.

304
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:37,480
You don't need to worry about me.

305
00:18:40,580 --> 00:18:41,980
When you're in France...

306
00:18:52,060 --> 00:18:54,630
When you're alone in France in the future,

307
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:00,440
you'll have to

308
00:19:02,430 --> 00:19:03,690
take care of yourself.

309
00:19:10,030 --> 00:19:10,830
I will.

310
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:21,030
Xiaoman, go home.

311
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:25,750
Hang up now.

312
00:19:29,460 --> 00:19:30,820
You must be well.

313
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:40,480
Xiaoman, keep me company until the end.

314
00:20:32,350 --> 00:20:33,160
Are you home?

315
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:38,140
Uncle Ding.

316
00:20:38,240 --> 00:20:39,240
Come in. Come in and have a seat.

317
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:39,960
I won't come in.

318
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:41,690
Come out. I need a word with you.

319
00:20:42,030 --> 00:20:42,550
Lulu.

320
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:44,400
I'm going to chat
with Uncle Ding outside for a bit.

321
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:45,070
Go ahead.

322
00:20:51,190 --> 00:20:52,650
What's wrong, Uncle Ding?

323
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:53,830
Is Lulu home?

324
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:54,590
She is.

325
00:20:55,640 --> 00:20:57,270
Has Xiaoman contacted you recently?

326
00:20:57,270 --> 00:20:58,240
No.

327
00:20:58,510 --> 00:20:59,970
We can't reach him either.

328
00:21:01,310 --> 00:21:03,370
But Zhuang Sen told me a few months ago

329
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:05,550
that he was busy over there.

330
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:07,030
That's all.

331
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:08,350
But no matter how busy he is,

332
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:10,240
how can he not have time for a phone call?

333
00:21:10,240 --> 00:21:12,500
If he weren't busy, he would have called.

334
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:14,200
You're no help.

335
00:21:15,030 --> 00:21:17,090
None of these kids saves me any worry.

336
00:21:19,190 --> 00:21:20,590
Alright, I'm going back.

337
00:21:21,140 --> 00:21:22,720
Wait, let's have a drink.

338
00:21:22,750 --> 00:21:24,480
Drink what? You can't hold your liquor.

339
00:21:24,480 --> 00:21:25,440
Go back inside.

340
00:21:25,960 --> 00:21:27,220
Take care, Uncle Ding.

341
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:48,680
Yan.

342
00:21:50,110 --> 00:21:50,720
What is it?

343
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:53,460
Has your Xiaodan come back recently?

344
00:21:53,830 --> 00:21:56,790
You want to ask about
Xiaodan and Xiaoman, don't you?

345
00:21:57,250 --> 00:21:58,370
What happened between them?

346
00:21:58,370 --> 00:22:01,930
I heard from her mom that they broke up.

347
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:05,880
They really broke up?

348
00:22:07,210 --> 00:22:08,900
Oh my god. Then Xiaoman...

349
00:22:10,590 --> 00:22:11,880
He's so stubborn.

350
00:22:12,440 --> 00:22:14,350
He went to Japan and suffered so much.

351
00:22:14,350 --> 00:22:15,480
How could Xiaodan just dump him

352
00:22:15,480 --> 00:22:16,270
in Japan like that?

353
00:22:16,270 --> 00:22:17,270
Stop shouting.

354
00:22:17,270 --> 00:22:18,400
Calm down first.

355
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:19,510
Don't give me that.

356
00:22:19,510 --> 00:22:21,110
Always acting so refined and bookish.

357
00:22:21,110 --> 00:22:22,110
Calm? How can I be calm?

358
00:22:22,110 --> 00:22:23,680
It's easy for you to say.

359
00:22:23,680 --> 00:22:24,590
Your kid is studying out there,

360
00:22:24,590 --> 00:22:25,880
sheltered from the wind and rain.

361
00:22:25,880 --> 00:22:27,110
My kid went to Japan,

362
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:28,510
living hand to mouth.

363
00:22:28,510 --> 00:22:31,350
And now he just gets dumped?

364
00:22:31,990 --> 00:22:33,510
Can he even handle that?

365
00:22:33,840 --> 00:22:35,880
I think you're the one
who can't handle it.

366
00:22:35,880 --> 00:22:37,610
Didn't you lecture me about it?

367
00:22:37,880 --> 00:22:39,200
You said Xiaoman was 18

368
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:40,240
and the kids had grown up.

369
00:22:40,240 --> 00:22:41,790
You told me not to interfere,
and I listened to you.

370
00:22:41,790 --> 00:22:43,030
I stopped interfering.

371
00:22:43,030 --> 00:22:45,290
Why are you being so overprotective now?

372
00:22:48,550 --> 00:22:50,150
Yan, I'll tell you the truth.

373
00:22:53,830 --> 00:22:54,590
It's been 2 months.

374
00:22:54,590 --> 00:22:57,250
I've been calling Xiaoman,
but he won't answer.

375
00:22:57,680 --> 00:22:58,400
And then

376
00:22:58,400 --> 00:23:00,030
Xia Lei said that

377
00:23:00,030 --> 00:23:03,030
he could still see him

378
00:23:03,440 --> 00:23:04,590
on the computer

379
00:23:04,590 --> 00:23:05,860
with the internet or something.

380
00:23:05,860 --> 00:23:07,320
But he just wouldn't talk.

381
00:23:08,350 --> 00:23:09,440
I...

382
00:23:10,070 --> 00:23:11,240
I'm just worried
something might happen to him,

383
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:11,820
you know?

384
00:23:12,030 --> 00:23:13,890
We both know Xiaoman.

385
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:16,550
He wouldn't do anything stupid, right?

386
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:18,690
Now that this has happened,

387
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:20,830
we have to give the kid some time.

388
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:23,160
Let him process it slowly.

389
00:23:25,790 --> 00:23:28,790
Xiaoman has only had eyes
for Xiaodan all these years.

390
00:23:28,830 --> 00:23:31,270
I'm afraid he won't give up
until it's too late.

391
00:23:31,270 --> 00:23:32,720
Listen to me.

392
00:23:33,480 --> 00:23:34,010
About...

393
00:23:45,830 --> 00:23:46,350
Yuki.

394
00:23:48,050 --> 00:23:49,480
I think the Jiangnan Machinery Plant project

395
00:23:49,480 --> 00:23:50,440
is pretty easy to handle.

396
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:51,440
Just do as Mr. Kong said,

397
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:52,910
and it should be fine, right?

398
00:23:52,910 --> 00:23:55,300
I heard that Mr. Fan is hard to deal with.

399
00:23:56,100 --> 00:23:57,100
Hard to deal with?

400
00:23:59,920 --> 00:24:00,850
What do you mean?

401
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:04,350
I heard people in the industry say

402
00:24:04,350 --> 00:24:05,550
that he is...

403
00:24:13,790 --> 00:24:14,320
Mr. Kong.

404
00:24:14,880 --> 00:24:16,400
I heard from the other team

405
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:18,260
that you gave the project to them.

406
00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:20,750
I won't keep it from you then.

407
00:24:20,750 --> 00:24:23,010
I did give that project to another group.

408
00:24:23,640 --> 00:24:25,920
Meng Ge and I
have been leading this project.

409
00:24:25,920 --> 00:24:27,880
Why did you
suddenly give it to someone else?

410
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:31,080
It's mainly because
this project has dragged on too long.

411
00:24:31,350 --> 00:24:33,680
I'm afraid of missing
the best acquisition window.

412
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:35,140
I also only heard recently

413
00:24:35,480 --> 00:24:37,030
that you and Fan Weijie

414
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:39,740
have some history together.

415
00:24:40,830 --> 00:24:41,360
Exactly.

416
00:24:41,860 --> 00:24:44,240
So during this time,

417
00:24:44,240 --> 00:24:45,750
if you continue to handle this project,

418
00:24:45,750 --> 00:24:48,160
it might negatively affect it.

419
00:24:49,200 --> 00:24:50,400
How did you know about

420
00:24:50,720 --> 00:24:52,780
the matter between Fan Weijie and me?

421
00:24:53,160 --> 00:24:54,440
Since you know about these things,

422
00:24:54,440 --> 00:24:56,000
do we still have to work with him?

423
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:57,510
And the acquisition price,

424
00:24:57,510 --> 00:24:58,550
why was it raised?

425
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:01,460
The loss outweighs
the gain for the company.

426
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:04,200
How does the loss outweigh the gain?

427
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:06,750
Are you using your experience

428
00:25:06,750 --> 00:25:08,150
to question my judgment?

429
00:25:08,960 --> 00:25:10,620
What happened between you two

430
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:14,040
cannot affect the project
and the company's interests.

431
00:25:14,040 --> 00:25:16,240
The issues he raised can be resolved.

432
00:25:17,220 --> 00:25:19,930
I don't need to explain
other details to you.

433
00:25:20,350 --> 00:25:21,160
In any case,

434
00:25:21,160 --> 00:25:23,110
I haven't let my personal grudge against him

435
00:25:23,110 --> 00:25:24,000
affect my work.

436
00:25:24,640 --> 00:25:25,920
If you want to hand this project

437
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:27,120
over to someone else,

438
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:28,660
I can understand that.

439
00:25:29,070 --> 00:25:29,750
But,

440
00:25:29,800 --> 00:25:31,880
please reconsider this project.

441
00:25:34,960 --> 00:25:37,220
Are you trying to teach me
how to do my job?

442
00:25:38,030 --> 00:25:38,770
Get out.

443
00:25:41,030 --> 00:25:42,240
Leave the proposal.

444
00:26:45,110 --> 00:26:45,790
Xiaoman.

445
00:26:58,430 --> 00:26:59,760
Go home if you're tired.

446
00:27:45,310 --> 00:27:46,270
About this...

447
00:27:47,790 --> 00:27:49,790
Did you submit it to the higher-ups?

448
00:27:50,400 --> 00:27:50,920
Yes.

449
00:27:52,640 --> 00:27:54,590
I am your direct supervisor.

450
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:57,790
You didn't discuss it with me,

451
00:27:57,790 --> 00:28:00,270
went over my head,
and stabbed me in the back.

452
00:28:00,270 --> 00:28:02,200
Is this what I taught you?

453
00:28:04,030 --> 00:28:05,550
I just resubmitted

454
00:28:05,580 --> 00:28:08,510
the valuation report for
Jiangnan Machinery Plant.

455
00:28:09,270 --> 00:28:11,550
It came from 3 different
valuation agencies.

456
00:28:11,550 --> 00:28:13,750
One of them gave a valuation of 5 million,

457
00:28:13,750 --> 00:28:16,410
while the other 2
identified litigation risks.

458
00:28:17,660 --> 00:28:20,250
The agency that valued it at 5 million

459
00:28:20,790 --> 00:28:21,990
was the one you hired.

460
00:28:23,640 --> 00:28:26,270
Are you suspecting that
I have some shady deals

461
00:28:26,270 --> 00:28:27,930
with that valuation company?

462
00:28:28,110 --> 00:28:28,920
I didn't say that.

463
00:28:28,920 --> 00:28:31,680
I just don't want the company
to suffer a loss.

464
00:28:31,920 --> 00:28:33,550
Don't put it so grandly.

465
00:28:33,880 --> 00:28:35,310
I'm asking you now,

466
00:28:35,640 --> 00:28:38,720
what is your purpose in doing this?

467
00:28:38,970 --> 00:28:41,970
I said I don't want the company
to suffer losses.

468
00:28:43,830 --> 00:28:46,920
Do you still remember
how pitifully you begged me back then

469
00:28:46,920 --> 00:28:48,310
to turn you into a wolf?

470
00:28:48,790 --> 00:28:50,000
Now you've learned

471
00:28:50,640 --> 00:28:52,400
and are biting me instead?

472
00:28:53,440 --> 00:28:55,480
You have a grudge against Fan Weijie.

473
00:28:55,480 --> 00:28:58,030
You hate him for ruining your career.

474
00:28:58,030 --> 00:29:00,230
You've learned how to play the game now.

475
00:29:00,480 --> 00:29:01,750
You got rid of him.

476
00:29:02,270 --> 00:29:03,330
Are you satisfied?

477
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:05,010
But what about the project?

478
00:29:05,590 --> 00:29:07,000
It's gone.

479
00:29:07,590 --> 00:29:09,480
I have not violated
my professional ethics,

480
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:10,790
nor have I let personal emotions

481
00:29:10,790 --> 00:29:12,120
interfere with my work.

482
00:29:13,110 --> 00:29:14,840
I've been loyal to the company.

483
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:18,060
Success or failure,
we cannot violate business rules.

484
00:29:18,460 --> 00:29:19,150
Good.

485
00:29:19,920 --> 00:29:21,480
You've finally learned

486
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:24,140
to make trade-offs
when interests are at stake.

487
00:29:24,840 --> 00:29:27,160
But you didn't make the right choice.

488
00:29:28,160 --> 00:29:30,070
You were too impatient this time.

489
00:29:30,830 --> 00:29:31,640
Look at this.

490
00:29:32,830 --> 00:29:33,690
Did your action

491
00:29:33,720 --> 00:29:34,880
affect me?

492
00:29:35,310 --> 00:29:37,160
Did it affect my position?

493
00:29:37,510 --> 00:29:38,750
Now look at yourself.

494
00:29:38,790 --> 00:29:40,720
You have no cards left to play, do you?

495
00:29:40,720 --> 00:29:42,350
In the days to come,

496
00:29:43,790 --> 00:29:45,920
you'll have to face the consequences.

497
00:29:48,110 --> 00:29:49,240
See it for yourself.

498
00:29:52,270 --> 00:29:52,910
Get out!

499
00:30:11,590 --> 00:30:12,510
What's wrong?

500
00:30:13,250 --> 00:30:15,110
Upset that Kong Peng scolded you?

501
00:30:15,240 --> 00:30:16,750
He made it sound like it was my fault.

502
00:30:16,750 --> 00:30:19,280
I didn't abuse my power
for personal revenge.

503
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:21,640
The project can withstand any investigation

504
00:30:21,640 --> 00:30:23,570
from its inception to the present.

505
00:30:24,110 --> 00:30:25,110
Was it wrong for me to hire a 3rd party

506
00:30:25,110 --> 00:30:26,400
to do a re-evaluation?

507
00:30:26,490 --> 00:30:27,220
Was it?

508
00:30:29,270 --> 00:30:30,400
It's Kong Peng.

509
00:30:31,510 --> 00:30:33,150
He went into investment banking
right after graduation.

510
00:30:33,150 --> 00:30:35,480
He fought his way
through a bloodbath to get here.

511
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:37,790
In your eyes, you were upholding justice.

512
00:30:37,790 --> 00:30:40,200
Although you avoided losses
for the company,

513
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:41,270
you might have also caused the company

514
00:30:41,270 --> 00:30:43,200
to lose a profitable opportunity.

515
00:30:44,750 --> 00:30:45,510
Alright.

516
00:30:45,830 --> 00:30:48,330
I heard the company is still
acquiring Fan Weijie's factory.

517
00:30:48,330 --> 00:30:49,440
He holds shares.

518
00:30:49,640 --> 00:30:50,790
If he sells the shares he holds for you

519
00:30:50,790 --> 00:30:52,200
along with his own,

520
00:30:52,640 --> 00:30:54,480
he can cash out a significant amount.

521
00:30:54,480 --> 00:30:55,920
Part of that money is yours.

522
00:30:55,920 --> 00:30:57,520
Don't you plan to get it back?

523
00:31:02,440 --> 00:31:05,000
Miss Yamaomo hasn't been here lately.

524
00:31:06,550 --> 00:31:09,550
Maybe Miss Yamaomo
is busy with other things.

525
00:31:10,350 --> 00:31:10,960
No.

526
00:31:11,590 --> 00:31:13,990
Miss Yamaomo has lost interest in Xiaoman.

527
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:17,340
This pawn has become a discarded piece.

528
00:31:17,400 --> 00:31:18,400
He's useless now.

529
00:31:22,400 --> 00:31:23,960
Maybe he's still useful.

530
00:31:26,370 --> 00:31:27,170
How?

531
00:31:28,590 --> 00:31:30,850
He's on a winning streak and in good form.

532
00:31:31,030 --> 00:31:32,510
A lot of people are betting on him to win.

533
00:31:32,510 --> 00:31:33,440
What if

534
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:36,160
he suddenly loses a match,

535
00:31:37,310 --> 00:31:39,110
and it just so happens

536
00:31:39,960 --> 00:31:41,830
that we bet on that outcome?

537
00:31:49,220 --> 00:31:51,350
Will he agree to throw the fight?

538
00:31:52,400 --> 00:31:53,800
Before, definitely not.

539
00:31:54,310 --> 00:31:56,440
But now that he failed to keep Yamaomo,

540
00:31:56,830 --> 00:31:58,270
he has caused losses for the gym.

541
00:31:58,270 --> 00:32:00,200
We'll hold him accountable first,

542
00:32:00,200 --> 00:32:03,960
then hint that throwing the fight
will get him a bigger cut.

543
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:06,030
I don't think he'll refuse.

544
00:32:09,640 --> 00:32:13,920
Right. Money reveals human nature best.

545
00:32:16,830 --> 00:32:19,510
What are you waiting for?
Arrange for it immediately.

546
00:32:19,510 --> 00:32:20,080
Yes, sir.

547
00:32:49,510 --> 00:32:50,300
Here again?

548
00:32:50,330 --> 00:32:52,440
You've been playing
quite aggressively lately.

549
00:32:52,440 --> 00:32:55,270
That Miyamura guy you beat before
is here to challenge the gym.

550
00:32:55,270 --> 00:32:57,330
He says you only won by luck last time.

551
00:32:57,720 --> 00:32:59,960
If you can knock him down this time,

552
00:33:00,120 --> 00:33:02,120
I can find you a bigger venue.

553
00:33:02,310 --> 00:33:03,880
We'll make more money.

554
00:33:04,750 --> 00:33:05,610
What do you say?

555
00:33:05,720 --> 00:33:06,580
Will you fight?

556
00:33:07,350 --> 00:33:07,880
I will.

557
00:33:09,110 --> 00:33:09,640
Good.

558
00:33:09,920 --> 00:33:11,830
As long as you're willing to fight,

559
00:33:11,830 --> 00:33:13,090
money isn't a problem.

560
00:33:13,360 --> 00:33:14,090
Come with me.

561
00:33:18,960 --> 00:33:21,160
10 seconds left in the 5th round.

562
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:23,110
Can Tanaka hold on?

563
00:33:23,960 --> 00:33:27,070
Rear hand! Miura threw a heavy punch!

564
00:33:27,070 --> 00:33:30,000
Tanaka is down! Miura wins!

565
00:33:30,960 --> 00:33:33,440
The challenger for the next match
is Miyamura Masao.

566
00:33:33,440 --> 00:33:35,830
He will face the fighter from China,

567
00:33:35,830 --> 00:33:39,110
Zhang Xiaoman,
who has won 10 consecutive matches!

568
00:33:42,550 --> 00:33:45,880
You are the son of Western Tiecheng
who loves your hometown.

569
00:33:46,270 --> 00:33:48,480
How can you leave your home for me

570
00:33:49,310 --> 00:33:50,840
and end up covered in scars?

571
00:33:51,920 --> 00:33:53,720
I don't want to see you like this.

572
00:34:00,930 --> 00:34:03,870
Boss, someone has placed
a challenge bet against you.

573
00:34:03,870 --> 00:34:05,670
Who is it? How much?

574
00:34:06,360 --> 00:34:07,560
An anonymous player.

575
00:34:07,790 --> 00:34:08,590
Double your wager.

576
00:34:08,590 --> 00:34:09,550
Double?

577
00:34:14,760 --> 00:34:17,280
Did he confirm he'd go down
in the 3rd round?

578
00:34:17,800 --> 00:34:18,400
Yes.

579
00:34:19,150 --> 00:34:22,440
I gave him a price he couldn't refuse.

580
00:34:25,030 --> 00:34:26,440
Okay.

581
00:34:26,949 --> 00:34:29,060
If anyone else bets, take it all.

582
00:34:29,550 --> 00:34:30,150
Yes, sir.

583
00:34:33,150 --> 00:34:35,670
First up, representing KOB Boxing Gym,

584
00:34:35,670 --> 00:34:38,670
Zhang Xiaoman from China.

585
00:34:38,840 --> 00:34:51,320
Xiaoman!

586
00:34:51,320 --> 00:34:55,480
Next is the famous Miyamura Masao.

587
00:34:55,840 --> 00:34:59,280
He was knocked down
by Zhang Xiaoman in a previous match.

588
00:34:59,280 --> 00:35:02,070
It's his revenge fight this time!

589
00:35:02,070 --> 00:35:08,070
Xiaoman!

590
00:35:08,070 --> 00:35:08,710
Start!

591
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:47,800
He won't go down
in the first round, will he?

592
00:35:47,960 --> 00:35:49,220
That would be too fake.

593
00:35:49,830 --> 00:35:50,560
Understood.

594
00:35:51,110 --> 00:35:53,380
I'll go down and remind him.

595
00:36:03,480 --> 00:36:04,510
Stop! Stop!

596
00:36:09,550 --> 00:36:10,150
Xiaoman.

597
00:36:10,710 --> 00:36:12,190
Fight with everything you've got.

598
00:36:12,190 --> 00:36:13,840
I brought you into this trade.

599
00:36:13,840 --> 00:36:15,510
I know best what you want.

600
00:36:15,710 --> 00:36:17,480
Watanabe gives us leftovers.

601
00:36:17,880 --> 00:36:18,880
But winning this fight

602
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:20,760
gets us our tickets home.

603
00:36:21,110 --> 00:36:23,280
I've bet my entire fortune on you.

604
00:36:23,280 --> 00:36:25,410
Miyamura Masao has lost to you before.

605
00:36:25,550 --> 00:36:26,960
There's no one else in the ring.

606
00:36:26,960 --> 00:36:27,440
Only you,

607
00:36:27,440 --> 00:36:29,760
and the chance to stand tall from now on.

608
00:36:30,110 --> 00:36:32,710
Do you want to go back
to East Chemical Plant in glory?

609
00:36:32,710 --> 00:36:33,630
Then win.

610
00:36:34,110 --> 00:36:35,170
This isn't a match.

611
00:36:35,400 --> 00:36:37,530
It's our battle to turn things around.

612
00:37:02,150 --> 00:37:03,960
Who would trust a gambler?

613
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:05,610
I'm sorry, Xiaoman.

614
00:37:16,670 --> 00:37:26,800
Xiaoman!

615
00:37:31,320 --> 00:37:32,520
Get Yu Qiangbei here!

616
00:37:32,560 --> 00:37:33,160
Yes.

617
00:37:41,920 --> 00:37:42,440
Stop!

618
00:37:42,730 --> 00:37:44,800
Boss, I looked everywhere,
but I can't find Yu Qiangbei.

619
00:37:44,800 --> 00:37:46,400
What? Move!

620
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:51,360
Xiaoman.

621
00:37:51,710 --> 00:37:53,400
Didn't Yu Qiangbei tell you not to win?

622
00:37:53,400 --> 00:37:55,320
Those who don't follow the rules
end up in Tokyo Bay!

623
00:37:55,320 --> 00:37:56,520
Translate it for him.

624
00:37:56,840 --> 00:37:58,560
Xiaoman, he wants you to lose.

625
00:37:58,590 --> 00:37:59,960
He's asking if you
don't understand the rules.

626
00:37:59,960 --> 00:38:01,800
And he says you should be prepared to die.

627
00:38:01,800 --> 00:38:03,000
I never throw a fight.

628
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:06,200
He doesn’t throw fights.

629
00:38:07,030 --> 00:38:08,960
I've bet everything on this match.

630
00:38:09,070 --> 00:38:11,030
You must lose this fight.

631
00:38:11,830 --> 00:38:12,540
Please.

632
00:38:14,670 --> 00:38:15,230
Xiaoman!

633
00:38:17,380 --> 00:38:19,130
Name your price! I’ll pay!

634
00:38:21,710 --> 00:38:22,510
Start!

635
00:38:37,420 --> 00:38:38,220
I think

636
00:38:38,700 --> 00:38:40,760
you and I are just doing the same thing

637
00:38:41,230 --> 00:38:42,510
over and over again.

638
00:38:43,030 --> 00:38:45,030
Maybe it’s time for us to wake up

639
00:38:45,630 --> 00:38:47,090
and live a different life.

640
00:39:09,340 --> 00:39:10,700
Stop! Stop!

641
00:39:11,230 --> 00:39:12,280
Damn it!

642
00:39:14,150 --> 00:39:15,760
The winner is Zhang Xiaoman!

643
00:39:16,230 --> 00:39:29,070
Xiaoman!

644
00:39:42,670 --> 00:39:45,230
Stop! Catch him!

645
00:39:45,230 --> 00:39:47,510
Pay up! Stop! Hurry!

646
00:39:48,440 --> 00:39:53,800
Don't run! Stop!

647
00:39:58,440 --> 00:40:00,320
Bastard! Hand over the money!

648
00:40:01,230 --> 00:40:02,800
Hand it over! Don't run!

649
00:40:03,230 --> 00:40:04,030
Stop!

650
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:07,030
Stop! Don't run!

651
00:40:09,910 --> 00:40:11,040
Hand over the money!

652
00:40:14,150 --> 00:40:15,510
Stop hitting me! Stop!

653
00:40:15,510 --> 00:40:17,630
Bastard! Give me the money!

654
00:40:18,180 --> 00:40:18,950
Xiaoman.

655
00:40:20,670 --> 00:40:22,840
Why did you team up with Yu Qiangbei?

656
00:40:24,670 --> 00:40:26,510
You think you can escape?

657
00:40:28,400 --> 00:40:30,550
The money.

658
00:40:32,590 --> 00:40:34,120
I'll give it all back to you.

659
00:40:34,460 --> 00:40:37,270
Let me go. I don't throw fights.

660
00:40:39,110 --> 00:40:40,400
Don't hit me.

661
00:40:41,030 --> 00:40:43,110
Let me go. Please.

662
00:40:43,110 --> 00:40:43,760
Get him.

663
00:41:58,010 --> 00:41:59,970
Someone's here! Help!

664
00:42:10,880 --> 00:42:13,000
If the police had saved him in time,

665
00:42:13,370 --> 00:42:15,710
Xiaoman wouldn't have ended up
with this condition.

666
00:42:15,710 --> 00:42:17,870
Ms. Zhuang, according to regulations,

667
00:42:17,870 --> 00:42:20,580
I have to repatriate
Mr. Zhang Xiaoman to China.

668
00:42:24,250 --> 00:42:29,120
[East Chemical Plant, 2007]

669
00:42:33,050 --> 00:42:35,700
[East Integrated Chemical Plant]
